{
  "thread_id": "first-proof-p9",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "id": "p9-problem",
      "node_type": "question",
      "post_id": 9,
      "body_text": "Given n>=5 generic 3x4 matrices, Q^(abgd)_{ijkl} = det[rows]. Does a polynomial map F (camera-independent, bounded degree) detect rank-1 scaling lambda = u⊗v⊗w⊗x?",
      "score": 0,
      "creation_date": "2026-02-11",
      "parent_post_id": null
    },
    {
      "id": "p9-s1",
      "node_type": "answer",
      "post_id": 901,
      "body_text": "Bilinear form reduction: fix (gamma,k) and (delta,l). omega(p,q) = det[p;q;c;d] is alternating bilinear on R^4 with rank 2 (Hodge dual of simple 2-form c∧d).",
      "score": 0,
      "creation_date": "2026-02-11",
      "parent_post_id": 9
    },
    {
      "id": "p9-s1a",
      "node_type": "comment",
      "post_id": 9011,
      "body_text": "Null space of omega is span{c,d}; omega induces non-degenerate alternating form on V/span{c,d} ≅ R^2.",
      "score": 0,
      "creation_date": "2026-02-11",
      "parent_post_id": 901
    },
    {
      "id": "p9-s2",
      "node_type": "answer",
      "post_id": 902,
      "body_text": "3x3 minor formulation: rank-2 bilinear form => all 3x3 minors det[omega(p_m,q_n)]_{3x3} = 0 for any choice of 6 camera-row pairs. This is degree-3, camera-independent.",
      "score": 0,
      "creation_date": "2026-02-11",
      "parent_post_id": 9
    },
    {
      "id": "p9-s3",
      "node_type": "answer",
      "post_id": 903,
      "body_text": "Rank-1 scaling preserves vanishing: if lambda = u⊗v⊗w⊗x, then Lambda_{mn} = u_{a_m} v_{b_n} w_g x_d has matrix rank 1. M = Lambda ∘ Omega => rank(M) = rank(Omega) = 2 < 3.",
      "score": 0,
      "creation_date": "2026-02-11",
      "parent_post_id": 9
    },
    {
      "id": "p9-s3a",
      "node_type": "comment",
      "post_id": 9031,
      "body_text": "Hadamard product with rank-1 matrix = row/column scaling: M = diag(u) Omega diag(v) * const, preserving rank.",
      "score": 0,
      "creation_date": "2026-02-11",
      "parent_post_id": 903
    },
    {
      "id": "p9-s4",
      "node_type": "answer",
      "post_id": 904,
      "body_text": "Converse via polynomial nonvanishing: define P(cameras) = det(Lambda∘Omega). Explicit witness (n=5, lambda=1 except lambda_{1234}=2, verified non-rank-1) gives det(M)=-24≠0, so P is not the zero polynomial. Zariski genericity completes the converse.",
      "score": 0,
      "creation_date": "2026-02-11",
      "parent_post_id": 9
    },
    {
      "id": "p9-s4a",
      "node_type": "comment",
      "post_id": 9041,
      "body_text": "Zariski-genericity: det(Lambda ∘ Omega) = 0 for ALL row/column triples is a polynomial condition on cameras that doesn't vanish identically; fails generically.",
      "score": 0,
      "creation_date": "2026-02-11",
      "parent_post_id": 904
    },
    {
      "id": "p9-s5",
      "node_type": "answer",
      "post_id": 905,
      "body_text": "All matricizations: test (1,2) vs (3,4), (1,3) vs (2,4), (1,4) vs (2,3) by fixing different mode pairs. Rank-1 in all three matricizations <=> lambda rank-1.",
      "score": 0,
      "creation_date": "2026-02-11",
      "parent_post_id": 9
    },
    {
      "id": "p9-s6",
      "node_type": "answer",
      "post_id": 906,
      "body_text": "Construction of F: coordinate functions are all 3x3 minors det[T^(a_m,b_n,g,d)_{i_m,j_n,k,l}]_{3x3} over all mode-pair fixings. Degree 3, camera-independent, O(n^8) eqns.",
      "score": 0,
      "creation_date": "2026-02-11",
      "parent_post_id": 9
    },
    {
      "id": "p9-s7",
      "node_type": "answer",
      "post_id": 907,
      "body_text": "Geometric interpretation: Q tensors are quadrifocal tensors from multiview geometry. Rank-1 scaling = gauge freedom. F detects consistency with the gauge group.",
      "score": 0,
      "creation_date": "2026-02-11",
      "parent_post_id": 9
    }
